doc:
An Angular service, factory, provider, controller, directive, or filter.
Belongs to an AngularModule, and has a name, and a function definition w/ a list of injected parameters.
{@link https://docs.angularjs.org/guide/providers}
'service' type: function is a constructor; instance is what is injected into other functions
'factory' type: function returns value that is injected into other functions
'provider' type: function is a constructor; an instance of which is accessible to module config (w/ "Provider" suffix).  must have $get member which is a factory used when injecting into non-config function.
